MHSAA
March 12 at 10:07 AM ·

COVID-19 UPDATE (3/12 - 10 a.m.): Postseason events sponsored by the Michigan High School Athletic Association and scheduled for March 12-14 will be conducted as scheduled. However, attendance will be restricted at all events through this weekend, with updates to be announced Monday, March 16, for the remainder of the girls and boys basketball tournaments.

The MHSAA Ice Hockey Semifinals and Finals will be played March 12-14 at USA Hockey Arena, with Lower Peninsula Boys Swimming & Diving Finals beginning Friday, March 13 and concluding March 14 at Oakland University and Holland Aquatic Center. Girls Gymnastics at Rockford High School also will be competed Friday and Saturday this weekend. Girls Basketball Regionals Finals are scheduled for tonight, March 12, across the state, as are Boys District Finals on Friday, March 13.

Complete Information and Updates can be found by following this page: https://www.mhsaa.com/coronavirus

post_text: Raffle baskets are starting to pour in from the coaches. Proceeds from the sports raffle baskets all go directly to each individual sports booster account. So if you want to support a specific sport, seek out their basket and dump your raffle tickets in. Raffle tickets are sold in packages from $10 to $100. post_text:
Gala Auction items. Proceeds from our auction items go into the booster general fund. Last year we made close to $3000 on our auction items. These funds were used to purchase 2 new popcorn machines ($2500) We also assisted boys basketball with the purchase of new uniforms ($500) as well as new mats for the cheer team ($1000)

This is a silent auction, each item starts with a minimum bid. The auction will end at exactly 9pm on Saturday. Highest bid wins. Payments can be made in cash, check or major credit card.

Tickets to the gala are still available at www.lindenathleticboosters.com

Linden Athletic Boosters
November 26, 2019 at 11:34 AM ·

Finally!! The Linden Athletic Boosters now have an online spirit-wear store just in time for Christmas!

What's different about this store?

This is a 24/7 online store with high quality select Linden Eagles merchandise. All merchandise is none sport specific.

There is no deadline for any purchase, shoppers will pay shipping and merchandise will be sent directly to your home.

items will be updated and changed on a regular basis. If there is anything you'd like to see for sale please let us know. All proceeds from sales will go into the Boosters general fund and benefit all Linden Athletes.

You can access our store by clicking the "Shop Now" button on this page or visiting our website at www.lindenathleticboosters.com and click on the spiritwear tab.

Let us know what you think!!

post_text:
Gala Recap
Thank you to all our sponsors and 2019 attendees. We are proud to announce that the event was a great success. Thanks to all your efforts we made over $6000 for our athletic programs. This includes $3000 in raffle profits which were distributed to the individual sports accounts that provided raffle items.

We are already making plans for next years event. The date has been set for January 25th, 2020! We've listened to many suggestions on how to make the event even better. If you'd like to help plan next years event please consider joining us at our next general meeting on Tuesday, March 12th.

Please take the time to thank all of our sponsors, without them we could not have pulled this off.

Linden Athletic Boosters Gala Committee

post_text:
GALA INFO!! The day has arrived!! Some general information. Tickets are still available online and they can also be purchased at the door. We have made arrangements for a significant walk up so please consider bringing friends.

1. This is a fundraiser, please bring money!! We prefer cash or check to pay for any raffle or auction items but we will have the ability for you to use credit cards as well. We have a lot of great stuff!

2. Valet Parking is included with your ticket. Attendants will be waiting at the main door to the Camp Copneconic dining hall & event center.

3. The Bar opens at 5:30, we will start serving dinner at around 6:15pm

4. Coaches- Raffle baskets can still be dropped off prior to the event.

The Gala committee has worked very hard to put on a first class event. If you have any questions please post them here and we will get back to you asap. See you all tonight!!!!

Goooo Eagles!

I am copying this post from Chery Hawkins Pool, due to privacy issues I was not able to "Share" her post. It would be great to see some fan support for our Linden Eagles Marching Band!

"As a mom of a football player, I encourage all of the players to show up at the band competition this Saturday to support our marching band. They support the team by playing the fight song when a touchdown is made. Lets support them! They will be going on at around 6:45. Seeing players in their jerseys support them would be an amazing way to encourage our student body as a whole! Lets show them we as a community commend their efforts!

Hopefully we will have a strong fan showing to support our Eagle baseball team as they compete tomorrow in the MHSAA D2 Quarterfinal game vs Gaylord at 2:00 at Saginaw Valley State University.

Here is some game day information for those of you making the trip:
Gates open at 1:00pm for spectators
Parking will be in the North parking lot by the soccer field.....$5.00 per vehicle.
Admission=$5.00/person

The winner of this game will advance to the MHSAA D2 Semi Finals which will be held at Michigan State University on Thursday at 11:30 am. The final game will also be at MSU on Saturday at 9:00 am.

GO EAGLES!!

post_text:
State Bank Athletes of the Week

Congratulations to Kyle Korman, Alia Frederick, Kevin Bates and Liz Rakowski who have each been named as State Bank Athletes of the Week.
Senior Kyle Korman threw a lifetime best, 134" in the discus to place 2nd in a field of 47 throwers from 17 schools at the MSU Outdoor. Kyle becomes the first LHS athlete to earn Athlete of the Week honors in all three sport seasons.

In her first meet of the year at the Spartan Classic Invitational, Alia made it to the 100 Hurdles final and placed 5th (17.53a). She also had an outstanding race in the 300 Hurdles placing 3rd with a time of 48.08a.

Kevin had a outstanding week both hitting and pitching leading Linden to a perfect 4-0 record for the week. Offensively he went 7 for 13 (.538) while scoring 3 runs, batting in 4 RBI's and stealing 3 bases. Kevin also pitched and picked up the win vs. Swartz Creek on Friday pitching 5 1/3 innings striking out 4.

In league games against Sw. Creek, and in the Cheasning this week Liz Rakowski, was .562 at the plate, with 7 rbis and scored 2 runs. 9 for 16.

post_text:
Your Linden Athletic Boosters is hosting a Valentine's Barn Dance THIS SATURDAY February 14th at the Lazy J Ranch in Milford. 7-11pm ,. The Boosters will provide water, pop and appetizers. BYOB - coolers welcome $40 per couple/$20 per person.
You are GUARANTEED a great time!

Tickets available now either from Alison Davis (810) 394-5368, Christie LaFontaine 810-397-3438 or in the Athletic Office at the High School. Checks and cash are accepted. Make checks payable to Linden Athletic Boosters. Must have ticket as entry to event.
Lazy J Ranch
625 S. Hickory Ridge Road, Milford

post_text: We are so excited to share with all of you that we are planning a Valentine Square Dance Outing!! It will be Saturday February 14th with food, drinks, dancing, and lots of laughs!! Allison Davis is heading this event up and will have more information at our Monday January 12th meeting which will be at Planks @ 7:00pm, hope to see ya all there!

HAPPY NEW YEAR!!
Just a reminder the next Booster Meeting is Monday January 12th 7:00pm at Planks in Argentine. All nominations for elections must be turned in to Christie Lafontaine by this meeting. Elections will take place at the February meeting. Any questions please let us know. Hope to see you there!! Everyone is welcome to come!
